  "text": "The open-circuit condition is the baseline, where no circuit is attached to the piezoelectric actuator terminals. The short-circuit condition is when both of the actuators have a jumper wire attached across the terminals. K decreases with increasing rotor speed, indicating that the ability of our current actuator to control 1B mode also decreases with increasing rotor speed. More details of our spin rig experimental test on this subject are described in our complementary work (Ref. [CITATION_1] .",
